# Movie Search App

The Movie Search App is a web application that allows users to search for movies and view their details. It utilizes the OMDB API to fetch movie data and provides a user-friendly interface for searching and displaying movie information.

![Movie Search App Screenshot](/public/assets/logo.png)

## Features

- Search for movies by title
- View movie details including title, poster, year, plot, and other details
- Infinite scroll for loading more search results
- Clicking on a movie displays its detailed information on a separate page

## Technologies Used

- HTML5, CSS3: For building the user interface
- JavaScript: For fetching data from the OMDB API and handling user interactions
- OMDB API: For retrieving movie data
- Glide.js: For creating the carousel of related movies
- Swiper.js: For creating the image carousel in the movie details page

## Usage

1. Enter a movie title in the search input field on the homepage.
2. Click the "Search" button or press Enter to initiate the search.
3. The search results will be displayed as movie cards, showing the movie title, poster, and release year.
4. Scroll down to load more movies if available.
5. Click on the "View Details" button of a movie card to view its detailed information on a separate page.
6. On the movie details page, you can see the movie poster, title, plot, and other relevant details.
7. Scroll horizontally to view related movies in the carousel at the bottom.
8. Enjoy exploring movies and their details!

